column1: Click on a date for a map of all profiles from that day.
These maps show the locations of the L1B scans available from the ESA ftp site.
Coloured shading indicates orbits are present (see colour key below).

column2: coloured points represent positions where the L1B file records a valid geolocation. The absolute orbit numbers are shown along the bottom of the plot at the longitude of the ascending node equator crossing and the orbits themselves are coloured to aid identification.
